## Constraints and gotchas

- Modding for personal use is a grey zone in most jurisdictions; redistribution of modded APKs is clearly infringing on the upstream developer's rights and Play Store terms. Keep work local to the device it was built for. Do not redistribute build artefacts.
- BSD `sed -i` requires `sed -i '' ...`; GNU sed rejects this. Detect with `[[ "$OSTYPE" == "darwin"* ]]` if portability is needed.
- `apksigner` v1/v2/v3 flags must all be enabled for installs on Android 11+; v3 alone fails on some OEM ROMs.
